Author: Bharathan Rajaram

This is a response to a test set by Professor Benjamin C. Lok at the University
of Florida. I am an Indian and have no official affiliation with him. This work
is being done purely out of my own interest. Professor Lok has very kindly 
set me this test to help gauge my abilities.

Language: C++
Libraries: OGRE, OIS

This project is one possible hybrid implementation of  ratirisation and 
ray tracing. I am making the code public without any license. I hope someone 
finds it useful. Do mail me if you use my code. I'd like to know where it 
ends up.

DISCLAIMER:
USE THIS CODE AT YOUR RISK. I PROVIDE NO GUARUNTEES ABOUT ITS CORRECTNESS
SAFETY AND USABILITY.
